title: Houthi missile strike kills two civilian mariners, U.S. officials say
description: A Houthi missile struck the MV True Confidence off Yemen, killing two, injuring six others and causing significant damage to the cargo ship, officials said.

title: 16 children have died of malnutrition in aid-starved Gaza, health officials say
description: Sahar al-Zebdda was born in a hospital with no electricity. She died 47 days later from complications of malnutrition, her short life a chronicle of Gaza’s deprivation.

title: Everyone’s asking: ‘Where is Kate?’ despite Kensington Palace assurances
description: Catherine, Princess of Wales, has been out of the public eye since a surgery. A recent paparazzi shot and a British Army mixup fueled more speculation.

title: U.S. floods arms into Israel despite mounting alarm over war’s conduct
description: The U.S. has approved more than 100 weapons sales to Israel since the Gaza War began, underscoring Washington’s extensive involvement in the conflict.

title: Russian missile strike hits near Zelensky motorcade in Odessa
description: Odessa has been particularly hard-hit in recent days, and Zelensky has pointed to delays by allies in supplying air defense in contributing to the rising toll of civilian deaths in the city.

title: Starbucks Mideast stores to lay off 2,000 amid boycott calls over Gaza war
description: Starbucks became embroiled in boycott calls after it sued an employee union for tweeting, “Solidarity with Palestine!” The company said it remains nonpolitical.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Hamas says it will continue cease-fire negotiations
description: The latest round of talks on a deal that would pause fighting and release Hamas-held hostages for Israeli-held Palestinian prisoners remains underway in Cairo.

title: A century after the last caliph
description: It’s been 100 years since the world had a formally recognized caliphate, a disappearance that’s left a deep imprint on 20th-century politics.

title: Ukraine’s first lady declines State of the Union invitation
description: The intent was for Olena Zelenska to sit near first lady Jill Biden and Russian opposition figure Yulia Navalnaya, who is viewed with some skepticism in Ukraine.
